(a,b,c)
s
t
\gcd(a,b,c)=1
 \frac ab = \sqrt{\frac st} 
c = s.
a^2/b^2 = c/t
t/c = b^2/a^2 = (c^2-a^2)/a^2 = c^2/a^2-1 
c^2/a^2  = t/c+1 = (t+c)/c = (t+s)/s 
a^2 = s c^2/(s+t) = s^3/(s+t) 
a = s \sqrt{s/(s+t)} = s\sqrt{1/(1+t/s)} 
b^2 = c^2-a^2 = s^2- s^3/(s+t) = (s^2(s+t)-s^3)/(s+t) = s^2t/(s+t) 
b = s \sqrt{t/(s+t)} = s\sqrt{1/(s/t-1)} 
s = c
